UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393277900344
AB  - This study develops a theoretical model of the Eurodollar market with six assets and eight transactors. The model is used to analyze the Eurodollar multiplier and two controls on the Eurodollar market: a ceiling on the net foreign asset position of the European banks, and the reserve ratio on borrowing by U.S. banks in the Eurodollar market. In each case the analysis emphasizes the effect on the Eurodollar interest rate and on the U.S. balance of payments.
